<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>TEA Map 6.3 - MONITORING SITES IN TEXAS</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFCC88>

<A HREF="airch6p3.html#monitor"><IMG SRC="../littlebook.gif" ALT="Return to Text Icon" ALIGN=top  WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25><B>Return to Air Chapter Text</B></A>

<Center><IMG SRC="../almn.gif" ALT="Almanac Icon" WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60>
<H2><A HREF="../MAP.TOC.HTML">Texas Environmental Almanac Map Section</A></h2>

<H2>Monitoring Sites in Texas, 1995
</H2>
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="../line.gif" ALT="Line" WIDTH="100%"></CENTER><p>
</CENTER>

<center><IMG SRC="m.monitor.gif"  WIDTH=346 HEIGHT=322 BORDER=4 ALIGN= middle ALT="MONITORING SITES IN TEXAS MAP">
</center><p>
<p>
<UL type=square>
	<LI>  Sites Measuring Criteria Pollutants (Total: 64)
</UL>

<UL type=circle>
	<LI>  Sites Measuring Air Toxics (Total: 21)
</UL>

<P>
Criteria Pollutants, established by the EPA, are carbon monoxide, sulfur dioxide, nitrogen dioxide, lead, respirable particulate matter and ozone.
<P>
<I>Source: Texas Air Control Board, </I>Air Quality in Texas: 1992 and Beyond, <I>(Austin: TACB, 1993), 4.</I>
<P>



<P><P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../line.gif" ALT="Line" WIDTH="100%"></CENTER><p>
