<HTML>
<HEAD>

<TITLE>Voices of the Earth</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF>



<IMG SRC="images/folio.gif" ALT="GreenBeat!" ALIGN=top WIDTH=456 HEIGHT=72><BR>
<P>



<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2><BR> 

</CENTER>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>


&nbsp;<BR>

<FONT SIZE=+2>
<CENTER>Voices of the Earth</FONT><P>
<font size=+1> 
Let the Voices of the Earth come together as one Voice<BR>
And speak the Truth of Love throughout this land.<BR>
Let the power of our words create Beauty once again<BR>
As we work together singing hand in hand.<P>

Voices, voices. Yours and mine and everyone's.<BR>
Voices, voices. Voices of the Earth!<P>

Let the Voices of the Earth sing together with one Song<BR>
That tells the story of our Sacred Home.<BR>
Let this Song be heard by people near and far,<BR>
No matter where they live or where they roam.<P>

We'll hear the Voices of the People,<BR>
And the Voices of the Air.<BR>
We'll hear the Voices of the Eagle, of the Raven and the Bear.<BR>
We'll hear the Voices of the Fire,<BR>
And the Voices of the Sea.<BR>
We'll hear the Voices of the Mountains<BR>
Here, with you and me.<P>

Voices, voices. Yours and mine and everyone's.<BR>
Voices, voices. Voices of the Earth!<P>

Let the Voices of the Earth be still just for a time...<BR>
And hear the simple quiet in the air.<BR>
All hearts shall come to rest and in this place be Blessed<BR>
And we'll bless this world around us everywhere.<P>

Voices, voices. Yours and mine and everyone's.<BR>
Voices, voices. Voices of the Earth!<BR>
Voices of the Earth!<P>

<FONT SIZE=1>Words and Music by Paul Levine<BR>
Copyright (C) 1995 All Rights Reserved<P><BR></FONT><P></CENTER><BR>

Paul Levine, a children's music composer/teacher in Ft.Collins, CO
submitted the previous song which he wrote a few years ago for a major
international eco-conference, Voices of the Earth.  Since it's use as theme music
for that event it has been sung by thousands at events around the country and the
world - conferences, schools, churches - even at ecologically-oriented
weddings!  He hopes it will become an anthem for Earth Day and the world-wide 
environmental movement.<P>

If you would like a copy of the sheet music, Paul will send them for free.<BR>
Send a SASE to:<P>

Paul Levine<BR>
116 N Washington Ave.<BR>
Ft. Collins CO 80521<BR>
phone: 970-495-0291<BR>
e-mail: paulevi@psd.k12.co.us<P><BR>



