<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>GreenBeat! Sprockets</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<IMG SRC="images/folio.gif" ALT="GreenBeat!" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=456 
HEIGHT=72><BR>

<H2>Creative Events from Earth Day 1970</H2>

<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="images/tinyglobe.gif" WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=17 ALT="Globe">
University of Washington, students put out a bucket of oil and
invited onlookers to dip their hands in it so they'd know how it felt to be
a bird caught in an offshore oil slick.
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="images/tinyglobe.gif" WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=17 ALT="Globe">
Students held "Trash-Ins" or "Dump-Ins" in which refuse was collected for
return to the companies which originally produced it. In one case, activists piled thousands of no-return Coke bottles on the steps of the
soft drink manufacturer's headquarters.
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="images/tinyglobe.gif" WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=17 ALT="Globe">
Students picketed supermarkets that sold products in non-returnable containers.
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="images/tinyglobe.gif" WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=17 ALT="Globe">
Miami Beach brought out its parade floats, loaded them with garbage and gas
masked students for a "Dead Orange Parade."
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="images/tinyglobe.gif" WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=17 ALT="Globe">
A giant junk sculpture, welded together from more than 600 leftovers of the
American technology, occupied the 40 foot platform of a flatbed truck in
Union Square. Teen-agers in a charter bus had followed it down from upstate
NY stopping in other towns along the way to pick up more junk.
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="images/tinyglobe.gif" WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=17 ALT="Globe">
 In Hoboken 1,000 people symbolically dumped into the Hudson River a coffin
containing the names of America's polluted rivers. Then they symbolically
resurrected the polluted dead, to show it could be done.
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="images/tinyglobe.gif" WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=17 ALT="Globe">
100 students rode down a freeway on horseback demonstration against auto fumes.

<P>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="images/tinyglobe.gif" WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=17 ALT="Globe">
Berkeley students marched from San Francisco to Los Angeles in a 500 mile
"Survival Walk. " They inspected pollution along the way and shouted the
environmental message, exhorting students and citizens to get involved.
<P>
</FONT>
(Thanks to Carolyn Chase at the Earth Day Network for collecting the above examples.)<P>

