<HEAD>

<TITLE>GreenBeat! Sprockets</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<IMG SRC="images/folio1.gif" ALT="GreenBeat!" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=456 
HEIGHT=72><BR>

<H2>Water-Related Facts</H2>

<IMG SRC="images/droplet.gif" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=8 VSPACE=10 WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=24>
The EPA estimates that each American household generates 20 pounds of
home-chemical waste each year, much of which is disposed of improperly and ends
up in rivers, lakes and aquifers.<P>

<IMG SRC="images/droplet.gif" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=8 VSPACE=6  WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=24>
Evaporation purifies water, changing it from liquid into vapor, but concentrates 
pollutants in the water which remain unevaporated. <P>


<IMG SRC="images/droplet.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE HSPACE=8 WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=24>
An adult drinks about 2 liters of water a day. <P>

<IMG SRC="images/droplet.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE HSPACE=8 WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=24>
<EM>When the well's dry, we know the worth of water.</EM> <CITE>-
Benjamin Franklin</CITE> <P>

<IMG SRC="images/droplet.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE HSPACE=8 WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=24>
Water makes up 70% of the planet's surface area. <P>

<IMG SRC="images/droplet.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE HSPACE=8 WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=24>
Only 3% of the earth's water is freshwater. <P>

<IMG SRC="images/droplet.gif" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=8 VSPACE=6  WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=24>
The world's available water per capita has decreased by more than one-third since
1970 due to the more than 1.8 billion peopled added to the planet since then. <P>

<IMG SRC="images/droplet.gif" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=8 VSPACE=6  WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=24>
Using drip- or micro-irrigation systems tremendously reduces agricultural water use and
can acheive an astounding 95% efficiency rate.<P>

<IMG SRC="images/droplet.gif" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=8 VSPACE=10  WIDTH=19 HEIGHT=24>
The overuse of groundwater -- pumping out water faster than it is naturally recharged
 -- is causing water shortages in many regions of the 
 world, including much of China, Africa, and the Western United States. In Mexico City,
 water pumping exceeds recharge rate by 80%, causing buildings to sink.<P>

