<center><TABLE BORDER=3 WIDTH = "85%"><TH COLSPAN=3>LEGEND</TH>
<TR><TD>Shaded (darker color) Areas:</TD><TH> 
Outcrop</TH><TD>
That part of a water-bearing rocklayer which appears at the land surface.</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>Ruled (ligther color) Areas:</TD><TH>
Downdip</TH><TD>
That part of a water-bearing rock layer which dips below other rock layers.</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
