<H2><A HREF="../MAP.TOC.HTML">Texas Environmental Almanac Map Section</A></h2>

<H2>Texas Coal Mining Operations
</H2>
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="../line.gif" ALT="Line" WIDTH="100%"></CENTER><p>
</CENTER>

<center><IMG SRC="m.coal.gif" WIDTH=342 HEIGHT=322 BORDER=4 ALIGN= middle ALT="TEXAS COAL MINING OPERATIONS MAP">
</center><p>
<p>
<H3>PERMITTED COAL MINING OPERATIONS
</H3><P>
Aluminum Company of America (Sandow)<BR>
American Norit Company, Inc. (Darco)<BR>
Amistad Fuel Company, Inc. (Little Bull Creek)<BR>
Farco Mining of Texas (Palafox)<BR>
Farco Mining of Texas (Rachal)<BR>
Lower Colorado River Authority (Powell Bend)<BR>
Northwestern Resources Company (Jewett)<BR>
Phillips Coal Company (Calvert)<BR>
The Sabine Mining Company (South Hallsville)<BR>
San Miguel Electric Cooperative, Inc. (San Miguel Mines)<BR>
Texas Municipal Power Agency (Gibbons Creek Mines)<BR>
Texas Utilities Mining Company (Big Brown)
<BR>
Texas Utilities Mining Company (Martin Lakes Mines)
<BR>
Texas Utilities Mining Company (Monticello Mines)
<BR>
Texas Utilities Mining Company (Monticello B-2)
<BR>
Texas Utilities Mining Company (Oak Hill)
<BR>
Texas Utilities Mining Company (Twin Oak)*
<P>
*Support facility
<P>
Source: Railroad Commission of Texas, Surface Mining and Reclamation Division, Coal Mining Operations Fact Sheet, June 1993.
<P>
